1
00:00:01,240 --> 00:00:02,610
(Episode 98)

2
00:00:02,670 --> 00:00:03,780
Welcome.

3
00:00:03,910 --> 00:00:07,480
Oh my goodness. It's like a palace.

4
00:00:09,450 --> 00:00:12,650
Mom, this is our grandfather.
Go on, say hello.

5
00:00:13,550 --> 00:00:17,190
- Ok Hee and Tok Hee's grandfather?
- Yes. He's our grandfather.

6
00:00:18,390 --> 00:00:19,860
Hello.

7
00:00:20,460 --> 00:00:21,990
I am Jung Suk Hee.

8
00:00:22,690 --> 00:00:26,160
Jang Mi is my daughter.
Tok Hee is my daughter too.

9
00:00:27,530 --> 00:00:28,830
Jang Mi is pretty.

10
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:34,470
- Yes. Welcome.
- Hello, Chairman.

11
00:00:34,810 --> 00:00:36,310
I'm Oh Jang Mi's older brother.

12
00:00:36,810 --> 00:00:40,350
So the side-dish guy is Jang Mi's brother.

13
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:44,950
Thank you for being
such a dependable big brother to Jang Mi.

14
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:47,320
Not at all. And please,
you don't have to be so formal, Chairman.

15
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:51,520
I'm the Chairman's wife.
You all know that, right?

16
00:00:52,290 --> 00:00:54,660
The lady of Dream Group.

17
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:56,390
You...

18
00:00:57,830 --> 00:00:59,560
You like Tae Pyung.

19
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:01,370
You're like a twisted donut.

20
00:01:01,370 --> 00:01:03,300
All twisted up like this.

21
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:06,770
Suk Hee, what on earth
are you talking about?

22
00:01:06,770 --> 00:01:10,410
- That joke is out of line.
- Mom, come on. That's not nice.

23
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:13,310
My mother doesn't know
what she's saying, Chairman.

24
00:01:13,380 --> 00:01:16,150
Exactly. It's not like that at all.

25
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:21,150
Suk Hee, I'm one of your regulars.

26
00:01:22,190 --> 00:01:25,360
Alright. Everyone must be hungry.
Why don't we eat first?

27
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:27,960
- Where's Seo Rin?
- She's upstairs.

28
00:01:44,780 --> 00:01:45,780
What is it?

29
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,510
Who said you could just barge
into my room?

30
00:01:47,550 --> 00:01:48,810
I could knock all day,

31
00:01:48,810 --> 00:01:50,250
but you wouldn't hear me
with those things in your ears.

32
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:51,880
Your grandfather wants you downstairs.

33
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:54,950
- Why?
- Your birth mother is here.

34
00:01:56,890 --> 00:01:58,360
It's Tok Hee!

35
00:01:58,760 --> 00:02:00,390
There's my pretty Tok Hee.

36
00:02:02,130 --> 00:02:03,830
Mom, let's go eat.

37
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:04,960
You come down too.

38
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:08,570
Who do you think you are, my older sister?
Stop bossing me around.

39
00:02:10,340 --> 00:02:11,470
Jang Mi is your older sister.

40
00:02:11,770 --> 00:02:14,610
Tok Hee, you shouldn't talk
to your sister like that.

41
00:02:15,940 --> 00:02:18,210
Why does everyone only dote on Oh Jang Mi?

42
00:02:18,610 --> 00:02:22,380
- Shit.
- No. Suk Hee adores Tok Hee.

43
00:02:22,610 --> 00:02:25,820
I think Tok Hee is the prettiest of all.

44
00:02:26,080 --> 00:02:28,250
My pretty Tok Hee.

45
00:02:29,290 --> 00:02:30,290
Come on.

46
00:02:37,830 --> 00:02:39,930
I guess Seo Rin isn't hungry?

47
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:43,670
- She'll come down when she's hungry.
- Be careful, Mom.

48
00:02:45,770 --> 00:02:49,170
Honey, blood is a funny thing, isn't it?

49
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:51,780
- How so?
- I'm talking about Suk Hee.

50
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,410
Even though she's in that state...

51
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:56,610
No.

52
00:02:57,820 --> 00:03:01,690
What I mean is, she may be unwell,

53
00:03:01,750 --> 00:03:04,460
but she knows how to be a mother.

54
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:07,890
My mom did a great job
raising my older sister, Jang Mi, and me.

55
00:03:07,990 --> 00:03:09,260
Exactly.

56
00:03:09,630 --> 00:03:13,770
Here at home, not even you
dare cross Seo Rin, right?

57
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:17,240
But with just this little finger,

58
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:19,470
Suk Hee had her
under control in an instant.

59
00:03:20,970 --> 00:03:21,970
It's delicious.

60
00:03:22,910 --> 00:03:23,980
Here, have some.

61
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:29,710
- Thank you. I'll enjoy it.
- Okay.

62
00:03:36,890 --> 00:03:39,160
Oh, my. Isn't this...

63
00:03:39,160 --> 00:03:43,060
your treasured Joseon white
porcelain tea set?

64
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:45,560
I heard that cost more than
300,000 dollars.

65
00:03:46,300 --> 00:03:48,070
Why on earth did you bring this out?

66
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,340
When my son Dong Seok got married,

67
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:51,900
I planned to give this
to my daughter-in-law.

68
00:03:51,900 --> 00:03:53,610
I've kept it safe all this time.

69
00:03:54,810 --> 00:03:58,610
It seems it's finally found
its rightful owner.

70
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,240
Grandpa.

71
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:03,850
Does this mean you're finally accepting
my mother as your daughter-in-law?

72
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:06,220
You didn't give it to CEO Chae.

73
00:04:07,350 --> 00:04:08,990
And you certainly didn't give it to me.

74
00:04:09,450 --> 00:04:10,820
And are you my daughter-in-law?

75
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:13,790
You're right.

76
00:04:13,790 --> 00:04:15,660
Not even the crumbs for me.

77
00:04:16,330 --> 00:04:19,430
It's so pretty.

78
00:04:19,860 --> 00:04:20,930
That's right.

79
00:04:21,330 --> 00:04:24,040
The person my son Dong Seok
truly wanted...

80
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:25,800
was you, Ms. Jung Suk Hee.

81
00:04:27,170 --> 00:04:29,470
If I had formally welcomed you
into this family back then,

82
00:04:29,540 --> 00:04:32,710
I can't help but think
this tragedy would never have happened.

83
00:04:34,150 --> 00:04:35,150
I'm so sorry.

84
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:42,120
My mom was so smart,
she passed the bar's first round.

85
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:46,790
I know.
I heard all about it from your father.

86
00:04:46,790 --> 00:04:48,630
Oh my goodness, it's so pretty.

87
00:04:51,400 --> 00:04:54,200
Chairman. I've come to get CEO Chae's bag.

88
00:05:00,910 --> 00:05:04,410
That man is evil. He's terrifying.
Get away!

89
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:08,880
- I'm so scared! Suk Hee's scared!
- Mom!

90
00:05:08,950 --> 00:05:11,320
Go away! Go! That man...

91
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:14,120
It's okay. Mom, calm down, please.

92
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:17,020
It's okay. Just calm down, okay?

93
00:05:18,190 --> 00:05:22,130
- You need to go now! Can't you see? Go!
- It's okay.

94
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,800
It's okay, Mom.

95
00:05:26,860 --> 00:05:30,940
Oh, my goodness, honey! Chairman!

96
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:32,500
It's okay.

97
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:35,310
Mom, it's okay. Look at me.

98
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:38,940
What? That old geezer Chairman Ma...

99
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:41,510
invited that stupid Jung Suk Hee
to his house?

100
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:44,380
Yes, and from the way
he had the white porcelain tea set out,

101
00:05:44,980 --> 00:05:47,490
it seemed like he was about
to accept her as his daughter-in-law.

102
00:05:47,550 --> 00:05:51,290
That's ridiculous!
Has that old man completely lost his mind?

103
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:53,620
Accepting Jung Suk Hee
as his daughter-in-law?

104
00:05:53,890 --> 00:05:56,060
- Does that make any sense at all?
- Please calm down.

105
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,660
How am I supposed to calm down right now?

106
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,000
But...

107
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:04,970
you came back empty-handed,
without my bag?

108
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,310
The moment Jung Suk Hee saw me,
she started having a panic attack.

109
00:06:08,140 --> 00:06:09,410
I was practically chased out of there.

110
00:06:09,510 --> 00:06:12,180
Jung Suk Hee had a panic attack
when she saw you?

111
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,280
Perfect.

112
00:06:15,210 --> 00:06:18,950
That sly fox Chairman Ma needs to see her
when she's not in her right mind.

113
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:21,620
Then he'll realize how unfit she is
to be his daughter-in-law.

114
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,720
Yes, it seemed that way.

115
00:06:24,020 --> 00:06:25,160
Regardless, I can't let this happen.

116
00:06:26,390 --> 00:06:30,130
I need to get back in that house.
If I just stay here,

117
00:06:30,460 --> 00:06:33,160
that little brat Oh Jang Mi
will take everything from me.

118
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:43,940
That man is evil. He's terrifying.
Get away!

119
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:47,910
- I'm so scared.
- It's okay. Mom, calm down, please.

120
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:50,920
It's impossible. Just impossible.

121
00:06:52,350 --> 00:06:53,920
I didn't think it through.

122
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:57,590
Her joining the Dream family
in her current condition...

123
00:06:57,590 --> 00:06:59,060
is out of the question.

124
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,800
You shouldn't try to get up.

125
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:09,700
- Lie down, please.
- I'm fine. Just give me my medicine.

126
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:10,940
Yes.

127
00:07:14,440 --> 00:07:17,340
What a shame
about that expensive porcelain set.

128
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:20,650
Three hundred thousand dollars,
gone in the blink of an eye.

129
00:07:20,650 --> 00:07:22,180
That's enough.

130
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:25,780
If you'd just given it to me earlier,
this never would have happened.

131
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:28,420
Such a waste, really.

132
00:07:30,090 --> 00:07:32,760
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

133
00:07:53,510 --> 00:07:54,510
Grandpa.

134
00:07:55,050 --> 00:07:57,010
Are you feeling any better now?

135
00:07:57,850 --> 00:07:58,850
Yes.

136
00:08:00,890 --> 00:08:02,990
Jang Mi,
I need to talk to you for a moment.

137
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,560
Grandpa.

138
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:12,730
You know Chae Hwa Young is the reason
my mom is like that.

139
00:08:13,030 --> 00:08:14,300
It's not my mom's fault.

140
00:08:14,300 --> 00:08:17,540
I'm not talking about who's at fault.

141
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:21,110
I'm talking
about your mother's current condition.

142
00:08:21,170 --> 00:08:22,840
Don't you feel sorry for my mom?

143
00:08:23,310 --> 00:08:25,080
She ended up like that protecting us.

144
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:27,610
And that's why I said
I'd offer compensation, didn't I?

145
00:08:28,180 --> 00:08:31,850
Use that money to find a treatment
for your mother first.

146
00:08:32,250 --> 00:08:35,650
Later, when you and Seo Rin
are officially named as my successors,

147
00:08:36,090 --> 00:08:39,090
your mother could become a liability.

148
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:42,290
- Grandpa.
- Don't take this the wrong way.

149
00:08:43,060 --> 00:08:44,930
I'm only thinking of you two.

150
00:08:45,830 --> 00:08:49,470
Jung Suk Hee is merely the woman
who gave birth to you.

151
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,800
She has nothing to do
with Dream or with me.

152
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,440
No, to be frank,

153
00:08:54,410 --> 00:08:55,410
I...

154
00:08:56,310 --> 00:08:57,910
have very negative feelings about her.

155
00:08:59,110 --> 00:09:02,010
If Jung Suk Hee had never met my son
in the first place,

156
00:09:02,350 --> 00:09:03,880
then none of this tragedy
would've happened.

157
00:09:04,420 --> 00:09:07,350
Why else would my son have had to go
to a faraway country?

158
00:09:08,290 --> 00:09:10,390
- The cause of it all...
- Then are you saying...

159
00:09:10,690 --> 00:09:15,060
that Dad's life and ours were ruined,
all because of our mom?

160
00:09:15,490 --> 00:09:18,430
I wouldn't be so extreme,

161
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:22,130
but I do believe she was the root cause.

162
00:09:25,040 --> 00:09:29,410
I won't interfere with you two
seeing your birth mother.

163
00:09:30,170 --> 00:09:33,210
But don't ask me for anything
more than that.

164
00:09:33,710 --> 00:09:34,710
Grandpa.

165
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:38,480
I think it's best to set clear boundaries
to avoid any misunderstandings.

166
00:09:38,850 --> 00:09:40,080
I'm just telling you where I stand.

167
00:09:41,350 --> 00:09:42,820
So try not to take it too hard.

168
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:00,270
My poor mom... What am I supposed to do?

169
00:10:01,340 --> 00:10:03,670
She's not even accepted
by her own father-in-law.

170
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:07,040
My mom hasn't done anything wrong.
Why is everyone treating her this way?

171
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,950
What is it you want to talk about?

172
00:10:13,050 --> 00:10:14,650
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

173
00:10:15,590 --> 00:10:17,720
If you're here about giving up on Jang Mi,
just leave.

174
00:10:17,990 --> 00:10:19,920
Love takes two people.

175
00:10:20,790 --> 00:10:22,090
It doesn't work
if you're the only one trying.

176
00:10:23,260 --> 00:10:24,330
That's not love, it's just misery.

177
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:25,900
That's an obsession.

178
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Shut up!

179
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:31,870
What do you know?

180
00:10:33,770 --> 00:10:34,870
Did you just hit me?

181
00:10:35,010 --> 00:10:38,010
What? So your love is the only one
that's justified?

182
00:10:38,010 --> 00:10:39,080
And you think yours is?

183
00:10:39,710 --> 00:10:41,180
When you're making Jang Mi so miserable?

184
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:44,220
Is hurting everyone around you
what you call love?

185
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,320
Why you little...

186
00:10:47,790 --> 00:10:49,390
I'm not going to take your hits anymore.

187
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:50,690
What did you say?

188
00:10:52,590 --> 00:10:53,820
I'm going to protect Jang Mi.

189
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:56,930
- I'll protect her.
- I'll die without her.

190
00:10:57,860 --> 00:10:58,860
Do you get it?

191
00:10:59,860 --> 00:11:01,130
She's my everything.

192
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:02,970
My everything.

193
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,000
Never once...

194
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:07,870
have I ever tried to take what I wanted.

195
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,440
I never even thought my turn would come.

196
00:11:12,510 --> 00:11:14,450
I've always given everything up for you,

197
00:11:15,550 --> 00:11:19,520
and I thought I was repaying our parents
for all they sacrificed.

198
00:11:20,320 --> 00:11:21,920
- Jun Ho...
- This is the first time.

199
00:11:22,450 --> 00:11:24,520
That I've ever actually wanted something
for myself.

200
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:26,190
The very first time.

201
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:31,060
And I will never give up
and see this through to the end.

202
00:11:32,300 --> 00:11:34,170
I refuse to yield to anyone.

203
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:37,770
I have no idea
why you're acting like this.

204
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:42,670
Jang Mi doesn't love you.
If you really love Jang Mi,

205
00:11:43,110 --> 00:11:45,210
you shouldn't be the one causing her pain.

206
00:11:45,780 --> 00:11:47,240
Do you have any idea
how much she's suffering?

207
00:11:47,310 --> 00:11:48,850
And you think you know her so well?

208
00:11:49,550 --> 00:11:53,250
That's not because she doesn't love me.

209
00:11:53,550 --> 00:11:56,620
It's because of you.
It's because of her loyalty to you!

210
00:11:57,390 --> 00:12:00,490
- That's ridiculous.
- I'll make her love me.

211
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:03,230
- So stay out of my way.
- Jun Ho.

212
00:12:03,230 --> 00:12:05,160
If you can't let Jang Mi go,

213
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:08,600
then as of today,
we are no longer brothers.

214
00:12:09,730 --> 00:12:10,730
Are you seriously saying...

215
00:12:11,270 --> 00:12:13,870
- you're going to disown me?
- You think the same, don't you?

216
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:18,780
- You'd drop me for Jang Mi in a second.
- No.

217
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:23,050
- I won't give up on Jang Mi or you.
- Cut the noble act, Kang Baek Ho.

218
00:12:23,780 --> 00:12:26,420
You always win people over
by pretending to be the good guy.

219
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:27,950
How could you...

220
00:12:29,490 --> 00:12:33,690
- How could you change so much?
- I'm done begging you...

221
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:35,560
and warning you.

222
00:12:36,060 --> 00:12:37,830
So stop pushing my buttons.

223
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:40,600
I will never let you have Oh Jang Mi.

224
00:12:41,530 --> 00:12:42,530
Got it?

225
00:12:54,980 --> 00:12:56,280
This looks delicious.

226
00:12:59,380 --> 00:13:02,850
- Did Grandma make that for you?
- Yes. Isn't it pretty, Mom?

227
00:13:03,890 --> 00:13:06,290
I can make you one too.

228
00:13:06,590 --> 00:13:09,660
That's all right.
Don't go to all that trouble.

229
00:13:10,630 --> 00:13:12,900
By the way, Jang Mi told me...

230
00:13:13,130 --> 00:13:15,770
that you were rattling off legal statutes
at the fruit shop.

231
00:13:15,970 --> 00:13:17,700
Are you starting to get your memory back?

232
00:13:17,940 --> 00:13:20,770
Suk Hee is smart. Suk Hee did a good job.

233
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:24,040
No, what I'm asking is,
how did you know those legal terms?

234
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:26,140
Are all your old memories back?

235
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:30,580
I don't really know.
The words just came out.

236
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:35,350
Sometimes Grandma is really sharp
and her eyes get all sparkly like this.

237
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:36,920
Really?

238
00:13:37,690 --> 00:13:40,260
This meat is delicious.

239
00:13:42,630 --> 00:13:43,630
Here, Bo Ra.

240
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,400
It looks like it's healing well, though.

241
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:54,410
Does it make me look ugly?

242
00:13:54,470 --> 00:13:57,310
No, you're the most handsome man
in the world to me.

243
00:13:58,740 --> 00:14:02,110
Still, I'm sorry for causing a fight
between you and your brother.

244
00:14:02,380 --> 00:14:04,720
I didn't say it to make you feel guilty.

245
00:14:04,850 --> 00:14:08,290
So many people are getting hurt,
including Seo Rin.

246
00:14:09,290 --> 00:14:12,890
That's why I think it's time
we put an end to this.

247
00:14:13,190 --> 00:14:14,490
Do you have a plan?

248
00:14:14,630 --> 00:14:16,560
I'm going to formally speak
with the Chairman...

249
00:14:16,790 --> 00:14:18,660
about my plans to marry you.

250
00:14:18,930 --> 00:14:19,930
What?

251
00:14:20,230 --> 00:14:23,000
- You're asking me to marry you?
- Are you saying no?

252
00:14:23,230 --> 00:14:25,700
Of course. You have to be my bride.

253
00:14:26,770 --> 00:14:28,670
What makes you so sure of yourself?

254
00:14:29,110 --> 00:14:32,710
- I don't like being taken for granted.
- All right, I get it.

255
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:34,510
I'll stay on my toes.

256
00:14:36,110 --> 00:14:37,310
And listen.

257
00:14:37,780 --> 00:14:41,150
I found out what the murder weapon
was in my dad's case.

258
00:14:41,820 --> 00:14:44,050
- What was it?
- A wrench.

259
00:14:44,220 --> 00:14:45,220
A wrench?

260
00:14:51,430 --> 00:14:52,460
By the way, Kang Hyuk.

261
00:14:52,860 --> 00:14:55,070
What did you do with the wrench?

262
00:14:55,070 --> 00:14:56,370
I buried it on a nearby mountain.

263
00:14:56,730 --> 00:14:57,740
On a mountain?

264
00:14:57,740 --> 00:14:59,440
I took care of it, so please don't worry.

265
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,640
No one will ever find it.

266
00:15:03,040 --> 00:15:05,910
Should I go to the mountains
and look for it now?

267
00:15:08,010 --> 00:15:09,050
No.

268
00:15:09,850 --> 00:15:12,020
Those mountains are huge.
Where would I even start looking?

269
00:15:14,450 --> 00:15:17,390
The partnership with the external vendor
is critical,

270
00:15:17,390 --> 00:15:18,960
so schedule a meeting as soon as possible.

271
00:15:19,190 --> 00:15:20,260
Yes, I'll get right on it.

272
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:21,990
Team Leader Jin.

273
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:24,460
Yes, General Manager?

274
00:15:25,230 --> 00:15:27,160
Let me ask you something,
on a more personal note.

275
00:15:27,970 --> 00:15:29,500
Do you still have feelings
for Kang Baek Ho?

276
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:33,170
I do.

277
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:38,180
But with Oh Jang Mi in the picture,
it's really hard to get between them.

278
00:15:38,340 --> 00:15:41,080
If you help me marry Jang Mi,

279
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:43,580
then Baek Ho will have no one
to turn to but you.

280
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:45,980
When he's having a hard time,
he needs someone to lean on.

281
00:15:46,150 --> 00:15:47,150
Really?

282
00:15:47,990 --> 00:15:49,590
What do you need me to do?

283
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:04,570
(Jang Mi! Could you come up
to the rooftop for a second?)

284
00:16:07,570 --> 00:16:08,740
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

285
00:16:21,350 --> 00:16:23,820
Oh, Jun Ho? It was you?

286
00:16:23,920 --> 00:16:26,790
Yes. Were you expecting someone else?

287
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:28,960
Here you go.

288
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:35,770
Have a seat. Have a cup of coffee with me.

289
00:16:44,010 --> 00:16:45,110
It's a beautiful day.

290
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:56,050
Jang Mi, what kind of shampoo do you use?

291
00:17:00,690 --> 00:17:01,830
Your hair smells really nice.

292
00:17:05,730 --> 00:17:06,900
Did you get your nails done?

293
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:09,600
- What?
- Your nails. Did you get them done?

294
00:17:09,670 --> 00:17:10,670
No, I didn't.

295
00:17:17,940 --> 00:17:19,240
This is so irritating.

296
00:17:39,560 --> 00:17:41,600
What are all these photos?

297
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:43,630
You are the only one in the dark.

298
00:17:44,070 --> 00:17:47,640
- I felt bad for you.
- Cut the nonsense and answer my question.

299
00:17:47,700 --> 00:17:50,470
- I asked you what this is.
- It's exactly what it looks like.

300
00:17:50,540 --> 00:17:51,680
What do you mean it's what it looks like?

301
00:17:52,480 --> 00:17:53,910
Are you saying Oh Jang Mi
is two-timing Kang Baek Ho...

302
00:17:53,910 --> 00:17:55,810
and hitting on Jun Ho?

303
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:58,780
Oh Jang Mi just uses whatever man
suits her needs.

304
00:17:59,050 --> 00:18:01,690
She's a shameless woman
who thinks she can have anyone she wants.

305
00:18:02,890 --> 00:18:05,920
- That's ridiculous.
- You need to get back to work now.

306
00:18:06,190 --> 00:18:10,060
Or Oh Jang Mi will take both your company
and your man from you.

307
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:14,400
This can't be happening.

308
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:19,240
Right. Jin Hong Ju is right.

309
00:18:20,170 --> 00:18:23,370
I can't just let Oh Jang Mi
take my company and him.

310
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:30,250
Mom.

311
00:18:31,080 --> 00:18:32,150
I need to see you.

312
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:35,450
My dear daughter,

313
00:18:36,050 --> 00:18:37,620
you've come to see me after all.

314
00:18:39,020 --> 00:18:40,360
Thank you, my dear Seo Rin.

315
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:41,760
You know...

316
00:18:42,890 --> 00:18:45,860
that I have a real birth mother,
don't you?

317
00:18:46,230 --> 00:18:48,100
Of course I do.

318
00:18:49,770 --> 00:18:51,570
I'm so sorry.

319
00:18:52,470 --> 00:18:53,900
While raising you,

320
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:56,170
I couldn't even show you
how much I loved you.

321
00:18:57,040 --> 00:19:00,780
But there was never a moment
you weren't my daughter.

322
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:03,950
You know what's ridiculous?

323
00:19:04,780 --> 00:19:07,420
Jun Ho is your son, isn't he?

324
00:19:08,190 --> 00:19:12,390
Were you trying to marry off your own son
to the daughter you stole and raised?

325
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:15,260
You were the one who wanted Jun Ho.

326
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:18,660
I was completely fooled by Oh Jang Mi.

327
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:21,060
I thought she was you, Seo Rin.

328
00:19:21,330 --> 00:19:24,300
So I tried to set you up with Jun Ho,
the man you wanted.

329
00:19:24,970 --> 00:19:28,240
Look at her now.
Oh Jang Mi pretends to care about you,

330
00:19:28,310 --> 00:19:31,640
acting all nice
while slowly stealing your place.

331
00:19:32,210 --> 00:19:34,080
She wrapped the Chairman
around her finger.

332
00:19:34,710 --> 00:19:37,750
The Chairman will put Oh Jang Mi
in your position...

333
00:19:38,020 --> 00:19:40,180
and never let you come back.

334
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,650
Now that he's found
his long-lost granddaughter,

335
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:44,520
he's only going to care about Oh Jang Mi.

336
00:19:44,690 --> 00:19:46,260
Quiet! I've heard enough.

337
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:50,890
Seo Rin, you have to listen to me.
It's the only way you'll survive.

338
00:19:51,300 --> 00:19:55,530
Oh Jang Mi is playing the brothers
against each other,

339
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:57,070
and testing the waters.

340
00:19:59,040 --> 00:20:01,040
And since she needs Jun Ho's competence
at work,

341
00:20:01,510 --> 00:20:04,540
she will never give him up to you.

342
00:20:05,110 --> 00:20:06,140
She won't give up on Jun Ho?

343
00:20:06,810 --> 00:20:09,210
Do you know
why Jun Ho fell for Oh Jang Mi?

344
00:20:10,480 --> 00:20:11,520
When you were away,

345
00:20:12,420 --> 00:20:14,080
Oh Jang Mi was really good at her job.

346
00:20:15,350 --> 00:20:17,550
Maybe it's because she grew up poor
in a side dish shop,

347
00:20:17,550 --> 00:20:19,260
she worked like her life depended on it.

348
00:20:19,820 --> 00:20:21,630
That's what Jun Ho fell for.

349
00:20:22,290 --> 00:20:25,960
Men like women
who are passionate about their work.

350
00:20:26,630 --> 00:20:29,700
The Chairman also says
Oh Jang Mi is competent...

351
00:20:30,070 --> 00:20:34,100
- and plans to make her your successor.
- Stop it.

352
00:20:36,040 --> 00:20:38,180
Mom, come home. Right now.

353
00:20:38,740 --> 00:20:40,940
I need you right now.

354
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,250
Okay.

355
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:45,020
So you believe me.

356
00:20:45,520 --> 00:20:49,420
- My dear daughter.
- I'm marrying Kang Jun Ho, at all costs.

357
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:51,420
Mom, make it happen.

358
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:53,920
I refuse to lose him to Oh Jang Mi,
you understand?

359
00:20:56,190 --> 00:20:59,530
That's my condition for working with you.

360
00:21:00,330 --> 00:21:03,930
I will marry Kang Jun Ho,
and I won't let her take Dream either.

361
00:21:11,010 --> 00:21:12,010
Mother.

362
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:14,780
You're here. Come in.

363
00:21:16,110 --> 00:21:20,320
- How did you get in?
- The door was unlocked.

364
00:21:21,820 --> 00:21:22,990
Where is my head?

365
00:21:23,320 --> 00:21:25,420
I've just been so out of it lately.
Have a seat.

366
00:21:29,790 --> 00:21:32,160
Ma'am, you must be so upset.

367
00:21:33,030 --> 00:21:34,060
I guess so.

368
00:21:34,770 --> 00:21:36,770
You're being so strong about it.

369
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:41,240
If it were me,
I would have lost my mind by now.

370
00:21:42,270 --> 00:21:45,110
It seems like Professor Kang
is still seeing CEO Chae.

371
00:21:45,410 --> 00:21:47,240
How could he do that?

372
00:21:47,940 --> 00:21:50,950
I get that he adopted
and raised her biological son,

373
00:21:51,180 --> 00:21:53,350
but now they're all laughing it up
like one big happy family...

374
00:21:55,920 --> 00:21:56,920
What?

375
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,020
What are you talking about?

376
00:22:00,290 --> 00:22:02,060
What do you mean, "one big happy family?"

377
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:05,660
It's nothing.

378
00:22:05,660 --> 00:22:08,700
"He adopted
and raised her biological son?"

379
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:15,410
Who did Professor Kang Nam Bong
adopt and raise?

380
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:24,950
Hong Ju.

381
00:22:26,920 --> 00:22:28,020
Tell me the truth.

382
00:22:29,020 --> 00:22:32,990
It's okay. You can tell me
whatever you know.

383
00:22:35,630 --> 00:22:37,160
Please, prepare yourself for this.

384
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:40,300
The truth is...

385
00:22:41,830 --> 00:22:44,170
CEO Chae Hwa Young's biological son...

386
00:22:45,870 --> 00:22:47,400
is Jun Ho.

387
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,640
What?

388
00:22:52,580 --> 00:22:53,680
Is that really true?

389
00:22:54,510 --> 00:22:55,580
You're telling me...

390
00:22:56,580 --> 00:22:58,780
that the woman
who gave birth to my Jun Ho...

391
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:01,120
is Chae Hwa Young?

392
00:23:02,050 --> 00:23:03,820
Yes. It's true.

393
00:23:05,960 --> 00:23:09,360
And Professor Kang Nam Bong knew this?

394
00:23:09,360 --> 00:23:10,430
No, wait.

395
00:23:11,190 --> 00:23:14,360
Did my Jun Ho know about it?

396
00:23:23,570 --> 00:23:25,180
Well, well, look who it is.

397
00:23:25,680 --> 00:23:27,380
What do you think you're doing here?

398
00:23:27,680 --> 00:23:31,980
You were kicked out, so why come back?
You think there are scraps left for you?

399
00:23:32,050 --> 00:23:33,280
Must you shout?

400
00:23:34,020 --> 00:23:35,750
Will you ever have any class?

401
00:23:36,390 --> 00:23:38,220
Then again,
I guess it's your low breeding.

402
00:23:38,390 --> 00:23:41,590
It doesn't matter what expensive clothes
or jewelry you wear.

403
00:23:41,930 --> 00:23:45,930
- Your words are pure trash.
- You listen here, Chae Hwa Young.

404
00:23:46,230 --> 00:23:51,070
You don't understand your place, do you?
You're finished.

405
00:23:51,270 --> 00:23:53,800
No, actually, you were finished
a long time ago.

406
00:23:54,140 --> 00:23:56,870
Do you still think
you're the CEO around here?

407
00:23:57,070 --> 00:24:00,610
Who do you think you are to talk that way?
Get out!

408
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:04,880
San Wol, what's with all the yelling?
Shit!

409
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:09,790
- Mom, come on, let's go to your room.
- Okay. You're a good daughter, Seo Rin.

410
00:24:21,430 --> 00:24:22,430
Is it true?

411
00:24:23,630 --> 00:24:27,170
That Chae Hwa Young
is Jun Ho's biological mother?

412
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:37,050
- I'm asking you if it's true.
- Come on, you already know. Why ask?

413
00:24:37,350 --> 00:24:39,880
- How did you find out?
- Is that what's important right now?

414
00:24:41,950 --> 00:24:44,820
How long have you known?

415
00:24:45,420 --> 00:24:48,590
Did you know it from the start...

416
00:24:49,330 --> 00:24:50,760
and had an affair with her?

417
00:24:50,830 --> 00:24:53,530
An affair? Don't be ridiculous.
Watch your mouth.

418
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:55,500
I'm asking you how long you've known!

419
00:24:55,570 --> 00:24:58,800
Hwa Young told me recently.
Why? What's the big deal?

420
00:24:58,900 --> 00:25:00,100
So then, Chae Hwa Young...

421
00:25:00,670 --> 00:25:02,570
knew about it from the very beginning,

422
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:05,240
and that's why she came after you.

423
00:25:08,380 --> 00:25:11,950
You didn't even realize
she was playing you. You're pathetic.

424
00:25:12,980 --> 00:25:15,890
Nobody was playing me!

425
00:25:16,250 --> 00:25:18,360
Hwa Young didn't know from the beginning.

426
00:25:18,360 --> 00:25:21,190
She found it out
after our love had deepened.

427
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:22,460
If you don't know, then shut your mouth.

428
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:25,000
That's just what you want to believe
because you're blinded by love!

429
00:25:25,060 --> 00:25:27,400
What do you know about Hwa Young
to talk about her like that?

430
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:31,030
Ever since she found out
Jun Ho was her son,

431
00:25:31,530 --> 00:25:35,970
she's been dreaming of
the three of us becoming a family.

432
00:25:37,310 --> 00:25:38,310
What?

433
00:25:38,780 --> 00:25:42,050
That's how sincere
Hwa Young is about our love.

434
00:25:42,380 --> 00:25:46,450
Stop bad-mouthing Hwa Young
and just think about the divorce. Okay?

435
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:49,020
Why, you!

436
00:25:50,550 --> 00:25:51,550
You!

437
00:25:52,020 --> 00:25:55,290
- Bad-mouthing her? You punk!
- Let go of me! I said, let go.

438
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:59,160
When are you going to snap out of it?
You worthless man!

439
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:06,440
Chae Hwa Young!

440
00:26:06,970 --> 00:26:08,310
Where is Chae Hwa Young?

441
00:26:08,970 --> 00:26:10,210
Get out here, Chae Hwa Young!

442
00:26:10,470 --> 00:26:11,640
What's all this commotion about?

443
00:26:15,050 --> 00:26:16,050
Lawyer Han.

444
00:26:16,750 --> 00:26:18,320
What brings you here at this hour?

445
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:27,860
What do you think you're doing?

446
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:29,160
What do I think I'm doing?

447
00:26:29,760 --> 00:26:32,200
Who are you to ask, you homewrecker?

448
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:34,600
There's a line you don't cross
when you're wrecking a home.

449
00:26:34,700 --> 00:26:37,700
You're going too far, Lawyer Han.

450
00:26:38,230 --> 00:26:40,540
Besides, what gives you the right
to come here and cause a scene?

451
00:26:40,600 --> 00:26:43,840
You're one to talk!
What do you think you're doing?

452
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:46,340
Wasn't stealing my husband enough for you?

453
00:26:47,010 --> 00:26:49,010
You had to plant your cuckoo's egg
in my nest?

454
00:26:49,850 --> 00:26:51,380
That's ridiculous...

455
00:26:52,380 --> 00:26:55,190
How could you leave your son with me,

456
00:26:55,250 --> 00:26:58,460
then have an affair with my husband
and ruin my family?

457
00:26:58,520 --> 00:27:00,390
Get off me!

458
00:27:00,860 --> 00:27:03,830
You don't deserve to be a mother.

459
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:06,760
You're not a mother, you're a monster!
A monster, you hear me?

460
00:27:11,230 --> 00:27:12,240
Lawyer Han.

461
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:18,980
I think there's been a misunderstanding.
Please, calm down.

462
00:27:19,310 --> 00:27:23,550
Just calm down and let's talk outside.
We can clear this all up.

463
00:27:26,380 --> 00:27:27,380
"Misunderstanding?"

464
00:27:27,780 --> 00:27:29,390
Don't give me that nonsense!

465
00:27:30,520 --> 00:27:34,890
I wouldn't forgive you even if you begged!
What misunderstanding?

466
00:27:34,960 --> 00:27:37,330
Han Young Ja,
are you really going to do this?

467
00:27:37,830 --> 00:27:40,900
You can't even keep your husband in line.
Who are you to be yelling?

468
00:27:41,870 --> 00:27:43,830
What in the world is going on here?

469
00:27:45,700 --> 00:27:48,370
Father, it's nothing.

470
00:27:52,540 --> 00:27:53,540
Chairman.

471
00:27:53,940 --> 00:27:57,280
Jun Ho's birth mother is Chae Hwa Young.

472
00:27:57,680 --> 00:28:01,480
Chae Hwa Young is the one
who gave birth to my eldest son, Jun Ho.

473
00:28:01,790 --> 00:28:06,120
- And you think this is nothing?
- What did you say?

474
00:28:06,520 --> 00:28:10,430
Kang Jun Ho is Chae Hwa Young's son?

475
00:28:41,260 --> 00:28:43,760
(The First Man)

476
00:28:43,830 --> 00:28:46,660
You're just a mutt
with some stranger's filthy blood.

477
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:49,330
You're fired. Get out now!

478
00:28:50,100 --> 00:28:53,900
Mom, what if that woman, Seong Sil,
isn't the wife but the mistress?

479
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:57,410
But wait. That woman looks so familiar.

480
00:28:57,670 --> 00:29:00,340
Put Jun Ho back in his rightful place.

481
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:03,350
Or perhaps I should expose
your entire slush fund, Chairman?

482
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:08,650
Go ahead. Do you want to bet on
who gets a longer prison sentence?

483
00:29:10,890 --> 00:29:12,890
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
